**Title:** COM - V.E.N.D. - SAINTCON

**Event Overview:**
- **Concept:** Introducing the V.E.N.D. (Virtual Environment Network Dispenser) Machine at SAINTCON.
- **Date:** October 2024
- **Brought to you by:** bashNinja

**V.E.N.D. Machine Features:**
- Provides customizable virtual environments on-demand.
- Attendees can choose from multiple operating systems including Windows 11, Kali Linux, Ubuntu, Debian, BlackArch, Arch, and Parrot Linux.
- Located in the contest and community space, available throughout the conference.
- The machine prints a receipt with login credentials for accessing a remote virtual machine (VM).

**Functionality:**
- **Customization:** Users can install tools and applications on their VMs.
- **Sharing VMs:** Collaboration allowed using TailScale.
- **Data Storage:** VMs are decommissioned post-conference; users should back up important data.
- **Restrictions:** Illegal activities are prohibited. Must adhere to the SAINTCON Code of Conduct.
- **Support:** A dedicated team is available for technical difficulties.

**Operating Hours:**
- **Monday:** Closed
- **Tuesday:** Noon - 5:00 PM
- **Wednesday to Thursday:** 9:00 AM - 5:00 PM
- **Friday:** 9:00 AM - 11:00 AM

**Additional Information:**
- **Cost:** Free to use
- **Self-Hosting:** Guides available for setting up personal VMs/containers.

**Expected Outcomes:**
- Hands-on learning and opportunities to practice skills in real-time.
- Increased accessibility to diverse computing environments for all attendees.

For more details, visit the event's webpage: [SAINTCON](https://saintcon.org/com-v-e-n-d/)